reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than the others I bought!
reviews.reviewText: I bought a few different mini fans for my famit to take on vacation to super hot humid climate and this one was the best. Battery life was the same for all the other versions but what made this one the best was that it was the most lightweight, the least fussy (one button), strong fan compare to others, and the blades were covered so didn’t hit my face/safer for kids. The other fans with exposed blades didn’t really hurt too much if it hit you but you couldn’t hold them under your shirt or close to your hair. This one was compact and safer and more versatile. Definitely the one we used the most and will be purchasing again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars PERFECT for festivals
reviews.reviewText: Kept this fan in my hand right up to my face while I was head banging and boy was that a game changer. It looks small and it is, but it was powerful on the high setting. It lasted me 5+ hours and then I charged the fan right off of my portable battery for the night shows. Since the festival, I keep it in my makeup bag and use it for my eyelashes and setting my makeup in general and it's great. Only downside is the button is easy to press if it is in a bag and it will just start running if something else hits the button until you go back in and turn it off. The button is just a little sensitive. Love it tho and bought it for all my rave girlies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great compact fan!
reviews.reviewText: I use this fan to dry my lash extensions. It's very thin and easy to hold and carry in your purse if needed. It's lightweight and holds a great charge. USB charging is the way to go! Great so far and reasonably priced.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these fans
reviews.reviewText: I bought a pink one a long time ago to use to dry my setting spray. I recently got another to dry my lash extensions after I wash my face. The battery lasts a week or two. I want another one to put in my purse for the summer. They’re good quality and charge quick.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Just wish the battery lasted longer!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this because I needed a fan to keep me cool while at Disneyland and while in Vegas for business. I love the slim design because it fits well in a pocket or in my purse. The lanyard feature is also a plus because I have the option to wear it around my neck. This fan is a lot more powerful than I thought it would be and kept me cool in the summer heat. The only downside to this fan is the battery life. It only lasted about 2 hours for me before I had to charge it. If the battery lasted longer, this fan would be perfect!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Disney in August
reviews.reviewText: These fans are the perfect accessory for a hot summer park visit. I have tried the cooling towels and this is a much better option. The cooling towels don't say cool for long in the hot Florida sun. These fans are very light weight, small, and the battery lasts pretty long. The main downside of these fans is they will need to be recharged at night, and the button is pretty sensitive so if it goes off in your bag this can run the battery down. Overall, well worth the money, and they come with a lanyard which makes them easy to cary around your neck.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is the best little fan out
reviews.reviewText: Out of all the little gadgets I've gotten on Amazon, this has got to be the best. It is what it is, a plastic fan, but it's very powerful for its size. I used it at a festival and never ran out of battery so I'm not sure how long it lasts but its plenty. It's also very lightweight and slim.Only down side is the power button protrudes out of the fan and is easily hit when in your bag so you'll often feel the fan turn on or not realize it has been running for a while.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Clutch for hot humid weather
reviews.reviewText: Several ladies bought this on recommendation for our trip to NOLA this July for my Hen Party weekend. This is so slim and portable. The colors are great. Its quite powerful for how small it is.I did unfortunately drop it on the steamboat and a fin broke off, bit it still works and moves a good amount of air even with that broke off. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewTitle: SE DESCOMPUSO EN UN MES DE USO
reviews.reviewText: SE COMPRÓ PORQUE EL TAMAÑO ES ADECUADO PARA TRAERLO EN LA BOLSA O MOCHILA. AL PRINCIPIO FUNCIONABA BIEN. DESPUÉS DEJARON DE DAR VUELTA LAS ASPAS, SE ATORARON. DESPUÉS EMPEZARON A DAR VUELTAS, PERO SE OÍA UN RUIDO, COMO SI ALGO SE ESTUVIERA ATORANDO ENTRE ELLAS. AL FINAL SE ROMPIÓ UNA DE ELLAS POR EL ESFUERZO Y DEJÓ DE FUNCIONAR. ES UNA LÁSTIMA PORQUE SU COSTO ES ELEVADO PARA EL TIEMPO QUE SIRVIÓ.
